{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id83d294b2-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s2309"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2309"},"text":"§ 2309.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Protection of constitutional rights of contractors","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id83d294b3-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s2309/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Prohibition on Requiring Waiver of Rights","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A contractor may not be required, as a condition for entering into a contract with the Federal Government, to waive a right under the Constitution for a purpose relating to the Chemical Weapons Convention Implementation Act of 1998 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6701"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 6701","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) or the Chemical Weapons Convention (as defined in section 3 of that Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6701"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 6701","children":[],"tail":"))."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id83d294b4-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s2309/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Permissible Contract Clauses","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (a) does not prohibit an executive agency from including in a contract a clause that requires the contractor to permit inspections to ensure that the contractor is performing the contract in accordance with the provisions of the contract.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id83d294b5-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3738"},"text":"124 Stat. 3738","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id83d294b6-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id83d294b7-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"id83d294b8-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2309","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"41:436.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/400/s40"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–400, § 40","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 39, as added "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/tIII/s308/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, title III, § 308(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-879"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–879","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 40, "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/tXIV/s1431/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, title XIV, § 1431(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Nov. 24, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1672"},"text":"117 Stat. 1672","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the reference is to the Chemical Weapons Convention Implementation Act of 1998 rather than the Chemical Weapons Convention Implementation Act of 1997 to correct an error in the source provision.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id83d294b9-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id83d294ba-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Chemical Weapons Convention Implementation Act of 1998, referred to in subsec. (a), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dI"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-856"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–856","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 75 (§ 6701 et seq.) of Title 22, Foreign Relations and Intercourse. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6701"},"text":"section 6701 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
